challengeName: Mnemosyne AngularJS Web App - Remember Selection Made In Interests Page
detailedRequirements:
We've been building a mobile magazine application over these past few months. It grabs content from all over the internet, aggregates it together, and displays it in a nice HTML5 front end.

The purpose of this challenge is to fix the issue for toggling interests, in the following screens.

Reproduce Steps:

1. Launch the app
2. Click on Menu -> Interests Page
3. Select some more categories to display in the home page
4. Navigate to other page and come to the same "Interests Page"
5. Selection made is not retained. It reset back to its old selection.

Expected Results:

the selection will retain in the app side, and the toggle should call reset api to update the interests in database.

here is the general rest api info.

@RequestMapping(value = "/interests/{categoryId}", method = RequestMethod.PUT)
@ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.CREATED)
public void saveInterest(HttpServletRequest request, @PathVariable long categoryId) throws InvalidAuthenticationException, ExpiredAuthenticationException, MnemosynePersistenceException,
MnemosyneEntityNotFoundException

@RequestMapping(value = "/interests/{categoryId}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE)
@ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.NO_CONTENT)
public void deleteInterest(HttpServletRequest request, @PathVariable long categoryId) throws InvalidAuthenticationException, ExpiredAuthenticationException, MnemosynePersistenceException, MnemosyneEntityNotFoundException

Resources

How to Test

Please test the app in iPad (Potrait and landscape mode) and iPhone (Potrait mode).
